    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/3–2251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d548fn1">Repeated to Paris for <gloss target="#t_OSR1"
                            >OSR</gloss> as 4960 and to the U.S. Delegation at Torquay as
                        496.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 22, 1951—6 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4302. Department would appreciate it if Moore<note n="2" xml:id="d548fn2">Ben T.
                        Moore, Deputy Counselor for Economic Affairs, United States Embassy, London.
                        Moore was subsequently assigned as an adviser to the United States
                        Delegation to the Special Session.</note> could be spared for period Mar 27
                    to 31 to participate in special session <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s at Torquay, on question creating
                    intersessional <gloss target="#t_WP1">WP</gloss> on <gloss target="#t_Eur1"
                        >Eur</gloss> tariff disparities. Dept believes most important Moore shld be
                    on hand at Torquay several days before Mar 30, when problem scheduled for
                    discussion, in order consult with interested dels.</p>
                <p>2. Believe presence of Hight,<note n="3" xml:id="d548fn3">John Hight of the
                        Office of the Special Representative of the Economic Cooperation
                        Administration (<gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>), Paris. Hight was also
                        assigned to the Delegation in an advisory capacity.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss>, at Torquay during special session wld be of
                    great aid to <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>, in view his substantial
                    contribution to prior negots this subj.</p>
                <p>3. Briefing cable follows.<note n="4" xml:id="d548fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
